What you need to know:

These are school going girls from Kimathi and Flamingo slums engaging in football activities and shaping their well-being and future by avoiding negative peer pressure which usually results in pregnancy and diseases such as HIV/AIDSMany parents who were opposed to the idea are amazed at how young girls have embraced football - a game traditionally considered a preserve for boysNgare reminds the girls to avoid people who tempt them to engage in immoral behaviours, as well as activities that compromise their dignity and future goals